                  <td width="560" valign="top" bgcolor="#C4EECE" class="style2"><p class="style79"><strong><em>Opinion Noted:</em></strong><em>&nbsp; A long awaited report was issued at the end  of June by the Massachusetts Post Audit and  Oversight Committee, chaired by Senate State Senator Marc Pacheco.&nbsp; The report follows up on a public hearing held last October 31,  at which then-State CIO Peter Quinn testified.&nbsp;  The report is highly critical of the process whereby the plan that  includes endorsement of ODF was adopted.&nbsp;  The Massachusetts administration, on the other hand, flatly denies many  of the allegations in the report, and continues to steam ahead, all as reported  in the two entries below.&nbsp; You can read  more about the substance of the report in <strong><a href="http://www.consortiuminfo.org/standardsblog/article.php?story=20060629235828586">this Blog entry</a></strong></em>.</p></td>
                </tr>
